OnUpdateAction.Code:
if ai.ActualQueuedActionsCount() == 0
	if position 
		ai.MoveToClosest("elevatorStart")
	else
		ai.MoveToClosest("elevatorEnd")
	fi
	position = ! position
fi

Handler.Code:
if collider.HasCollidedInDirection(0, -1)
	visual.SetAnimation("enemyHit", false, true)
	ob.Kill(true, true)
fi

OnUpdateAction.Code:
if aiControl.ActualQueuedActionsCount() < 10
	aiControl.PerformRandomAction()
fi

if obControl.GetXVelocity () != 0
	if actualAnimation != "run"
		obVisual.SetAnimation ("enemyRun", true, true)
		actualAnimation = "run"
	fi
else
	if actualAnimation != "idle"
		obVisual.SetAnimation ("enemyIdle", true, true)
		actualAnimation = "idle"
	fi
fi

if obControl.CheckIfIsMoving ()
	if obControl.GetXVelocity () > 0.5 && orientation
		obVisual.FlipYVisual ()
		orientation = false
	elseif obControl.GetXVelocity () < -0.5 && ! orientation
		obVisual.FlipYVisual ()
		orientation = true
	fi
fi

if aiControl.IsInRange("player", 10)
	output.Print("Grrrr... You are to close!")
fi

Handler.Code:
if collider.HasCollidedInDirection(0, 1)
	ob.SetAnimation("coinAnimation", false, true, 32, 40)
	controll.Kill(true, true)
fi

if ! collider.HasCollidedInDirection(0,1)
	ob.HP -= 30
	if ob.HP < 0
		ob.Kill(true, true)
	fi

	if collider.HasCollidedInDirection(1,0)
		ob.AddForceInDirection(250, 0)

	elseif collider.HasCollidedInDirection(-1,0)
		ob.AddForceInDirection(-250, 0)
	fi
	
	visual.SetAnimation("playerHit", false, true)
fi

OnUpdateAction.Code:
if obVisual.GetNameOfAnimation() == "playerHit" && !obVisual.CheckIfIsFinished()

else
	if ! obControl.CheckIfStaysOnGround ()
		obVisual.SetImage ("fall")
		actualAnimation = " "
	elseif obControl.GetXVelocity () != 0
		if actualAnimation != "run"
			obVisual.SetAnimation ("playerRun", true, true)
			actualAnimation = "run"
		fi
	else
		if actualAnimation != "idle"
			obVisual.SetAnimation ("playerIdle", true, true)
			actualAnimation = "idle"
		fi
	fi

	if obControl.CheckIfIsMoving ()
		if obControl.GetXVelocity () > 0.5 && orientation
			obVisual.FlipYVisual ()
			orientation = false
		elseif obControl.GetXVelocity () < -0.5 && ! orientation
			obVisual.FlipYVisual ()
			orientation = true
		fi
	fi 
fi
